16... Nxe3 17. Qxe3 Nxd5 18. Nxd5 Qxd5 19. h4
{ After a short, forced sequence of moves, White tries to spice up the position by generating play on the kingside, but his compensation will not be enough. }
19... gxh4 20. Nxh4 Qxa2 21. Qxe7 Qxb2 22. Bd5
{ White chooses a tactical option, but luckily we have a strong response after }
22... Bh3 23. Ng6 Bxf1 24. Nxf8 Rxf8 25. Rxf1 a5
{ We are slightly better. White's activity is what keeps him alive for now ! If we find a chance to calm the waters and simplify it would be good for us. However, be careful and do not oversimplify, evaluate the position before entering a drawish opposite-color bishop endgame ! }
