{ I believe this move has not been played before at high-level. It is probably a better move than any other alternative at this point. White's idea is to free the h1-a8 diagonal before taking on b7. }
17... Nb4
{ What a great move ! We block White's options on the b-file and have other ideas in mind with our knight ! }
18. Rad1
{ White can not defend the d6 pawn that easily without committing his position. An example variation would be the following: }
18... b6 19. Nd5 Nxd5 20. Qxd5 { The pawn on a4 is hanging! } 20... Ne5 21. Rd2
Qxa4 22. f4 Nd7 23. Qc4 Qxc4 24. Nxc4 Rad8
{ White does not have compensation for the pawn and black is clearly better. }
