12. Bxc5 Nc6 13. Bb5 { This is White's only natural development move. } 13...
Nd4
{ The idea behind this move is not to take on b5, but to centralize a piece and precisely to avoid Bxc6. }
14. Nge2 a6 { We try to provoke Bd3. } 15. Nxd4
{ This astonishing move is deeply counter-intuitive, but typical of concrete engine play. Few humans would think of it, as two of White's pieces will be en prise when Black recaptures on d4. }
15... exd4 16. Na4 { Pretty much forced. } 16... Nxa4 17. Bxa4 Be5
{ We target the pawn on d6, White is better off not giving it up. This position is highly unclear and extremely double-edged. }
