{ Whites second most played option. Probably Whites best choice after the main line: 7. Rc1. }
7... Qxa4 8. Nxa4 Bd7 { The best move according to current theory. } 9. Nc3 Ne4
{ Blacks whole idea is to increase the activity of his pieces by means of temporarily sacrificing a second pawn. }
10. Nxd5
{ The only move that can question Blacks approach. Any other ideas are logically refuted. }
10... Na6
{ Preventing Nc7. White scores really bad in these lines  (around 35%)  . This position has been reached in many high-level games, like for example in Wang-Topalov in 2010. }
