{ And in the following sequence  (rather forced)  , Black manages to keep good compensation. }
12. Kd2 Nbd5 13. Nxd5 Ne4+
{ This is an important in-between move. We prevent White from playing Bd3 after ...Bxd5. If that happens, we will not be able to play ...Ne4 later on. }
14. Ke1 Bxd5 15. Bd3 Nc5
