7... Nc6
{ Even though this is not the most popular choice at the top level, I decided to opt for ...Nc6 as it is more consistent with our repertoire and also rich in play and ideas. GM Avrukh defines ...Nc6 at this point as a 'viable alternative to the more common lines.' }
8. d5
{ White advances his d-pawn too fast. The idea of the 7... Be6 !? move is precisely that, to provoke d5 in order to undermine White's center with ...c6 followed by ...e6. Hopefully this will help you remember the right plan for Black in this position. }
8... Na5 9. Qa4
{ The most played option at this point. 9. Qc5 is also possible, but has been played much less and we play in the same spirit against both moves ! }
