{ Another option where we usually will not have many problems equalising and White should be careful in some risky lines. }
9... Ng4 10. Nd5 { The most testing attempt from White. } 10... Be6 11. Bg5
{ The only move that has been seen in practice as far as I am aware. } 11...
Ngxe5 12. Bxd8 Nxc4 13. Bxc7 { Too optimistic for White. } 13... Nxb2 14. O-O
Rac8 15. Bg3 Rfd8 16. Bh4 Bxd5 17. Bxd8 Bxe4
{ 17... Bc4 was played in Volkov-Mosadeghpour, Khazar op,  (2016)  . The game ended up in a draw. The recommended novelty is much stronger. We sacrifice the exchange, but we have a clear advantage thanks to our queenside pawns and very active pieces. }
18. Bg5 Na4 19. Rac1 Nc3
{ The a2-pawn will fall, or we will continue with ...Na5 if Bc4, which can not guard the e2 square and the a2-pawn at the same time. Black is clearly better. }
