{ The only serious attempt from White in this position, his king would be exposed otherwise and we win tempi and development. }
15... b4 16. Nb5 Nxd5 17. Bf3 Be6 18. Rd1 a4 19. Qd3 a3 20. Nd4 Qf6 21. Nxe6
fxe6 22. Rb1 Rad8
{ We threaten ...Nc3: a fork combined with a discovery attack! } 23. Qb3
{ 23. Qc2 could be possible too. } 23... Rc8
{ ...Qf5 is a strong threat now. The position is double-edged, however, I would play with the Black pieces in this position, I believe it is easier to go wrong here as White. }
