{ The absolute main line in this position is what I recommend. Other options are ...dxc4, which could lead to extremely sharp positions, and ...c5, which is interesting, but Black struggles to generate enough compensation in all the lines if White knows the theory. White has three main options at this point: cxd5, Bh4 and Bf4. }
6. Bf4 { Is not the best option due to the fact that there is a knight on f3. }
6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 c5 8. e3 O-O 9. cxd5 cxd4 10. cxd4 Qxd5 11. Be2 Nc6 12. O-O
Bf5
{ This is a well-known position which has been studied for many years and it is considered to be completely safe for Black. }
13. Qa4 Qa5 { a really practical continuation. } 14. Qb3
{ 14. Qxa5 transitions into an endgame in which Black is completely fine. See Zontakh-Timofeev, Voronezh op.  2014  . }
14... Be4 { this idea completely equalises for Black. } 15. Rfc1 Rac8 16. h3 e5
17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. Bxe5 Bxe5 19. dxe5
{ A draw was agreed in Gelfand-Kasparov, Astana  (2001)  . I would choose Black in this position, I believe we have a slight edge after }
19... Qxe5 *

