{ White's absolute main line. An ambitious move which poses Black some problems to solve. }
7... O-O
{ The main line is my recommendation here. However, I would like to bring 7... Bg7 !? to your attention. The idea is to play prophylactically against a possible e5. Black will enter positions with a great positional compensation thanks to two very strong bishops, Black's main aim is not to get the pawn back though. I would suggest keeping an eye on such lines. Unfortunately, there are not many high-level games yet, but it is likely to be used in the future. }
8. Nf3 { is not challenging for our purposes. } 8... Bg4
{ ...cxd5 is also possible. } 9. Qb3 Bxf3 10. Qxb7
{ White can not just grab the b7 pawn and survive. } 10... Bxd4 11. gxf3 Nd7
12. dxc6 Qa5 { This is really annoying for White. } 13. Rc1 Ne5 *

