{ This is not the right move order. There is not enough pressure against Whites centre and therefore our opponent can consolidate without the practical problems posed with ...c5 ! }
8. Be2 c5 9. O-O Nc6 { If ...Bg4, White can disturb our plan with Rb1 ! } 10.
Be3 Bg4 11. d5
{ And White has consolidated his position. However, imagine none has castled yet. Then the story would be really different with ... Bxc3+ ! }
