12... Bg4
{ Trying to consolidate the material gain, developing and annoying White. } 13.
Be3
{ It used to be very popular among GMs, but rather recent theory dismantled Whites plans. }
13... Nc6
{ The natural developing move is the best option. We also challenge the center. }
14. d5 { The main line and pretty much forced, the pressure is really high. }
14... Na5 15. Bg5
{ The main move at this point. 15. Bc5 transposes after ...b6 !? 16. Bxe7. }
15... b6
{ This is what I meant when I pointed out than Be3 was really popular in the past. This move was a major breakthrough, as described by Svidler, Black can simply ignore the Bxe7 threat and get a very safe position. 15... Qa3 is the main line. However, after Re1, we reach an extremely complex position and I do not believe it is practical to memorise long lines for the purposes of this repertoire. }
16. Bxe7 Rfe8 17. d6
{ Pretty much forced as the e4 pawn would be en prise otherwise. } 17... Nc6
18. Bb5
