19. Bxe8
{ Happened in the first game of the two played by Gelfand mentioned earlier on. }
19... Rxe8 20. dxe7 Qa3
{ We should not take on e7 straight away as White can annoy us with Qd8+ and Ra1. }
21. h3
{ White needs to annoy Black here, as if we take comfortably on e7 and keep both bishops, we may even have more chances than we think. }
21... Bxf3 22. Qxf3 Qxf3 23. gxf3 Rxe7
{ A draw was soon agreed. See Gelfand-Van Wely, Wijk aan Zee  (2006)  . We have an easy plan to establish a bind with ...Be5 and . ..h6-g5. }
