17... gxh4
{ This novelty line is enough to get a balanced endgame without risk. } 18.
Bxh4 a3 { Who cares about the e-pawn ? Our a-pawn runs too quicky ! } 19. Bxe7
Rc8 20. e5 Qd5
{ Our queen is very well placed on d5, where it has great options to play all over the board ! Also, it allows our a-pawn to keep walking firmly ! }
21. Rb1 a2 22. Ra1 Nc6 23. Bd6 Be6 24. Bd3
{ At this point, White's best option is to recycle the light-squared bishop to try and prevent our ideas. }
24... Bg4
{ We have the draw in our hands as Be2 is the only move that keeps a balanced game. }
