14. cxd4
{ The beginning of a sequence which allows us to equalise comfortably. } 14...
Qb4
{ Generally speaking, exchanging queens in the Grunfeld benefits Black, as attacks from White become less scary and our queenside pawns become more dangerous. This is especially true if White does not manage to have total control over the centre, which would prevent us from mobilizing our army from side to side comfortably. }
15. Qxb4 Nxb4 16. a3 Nc6 17. Bd3
{ ...f5 was played in Fordan-Szeberenyi, HUN chT2  (2005)  . However, the following novelty is my recommendation: }
17... Na5 18. Rb1 a6 19. Bd2 Nc4 20. Bb4 b5
{ Black has no problems in this position. } *

