{ This is the main move at this point in the 10... Bd7 !? variation. It has been played regularly by elite GMs like Vachier-Lagrave or Svidler. 11... b6 !?N is analyzed in a separate chapter. }
12. Bd3
{ A prophylactic, alternative idea which enjoys a similar popularity to Bf4. It is defined by Svidler, and I agree, as the central and most critical line of the whole ...Bd7 variation. }
12... Rad8
{ This is Black's main option at this point. This move seems to be the favourite option from Vachier-Lagrave in this variation. }
