13. dxe5 { The alternative does not give Black any problems after } 13... Nxe5
14. Bd5
{ This could be a better attempt. It has been highlighted in other analysis, but without showing a way to reply to this idea. I think Black can continue with }
14... Rab8
{ We want to continue with ...b5, gaining space and making White's light-squared bishop become sort of an observer of the position. }
15. c4 b5 16. cxb5 Rxb5 17. Qc2 Rxb1 18. Rxb1 Be6
{ I think this is the key move of this variation. We will see this idea in the main line as well  (spoiler alert !)  . In exchange for damaging our pawn structure, we exchange White's best minor piece in this position. }
19. Bxe6 fxe6 { Black is doing fine in this unclear position. } *

